    "eyebrow": "Frontier Lifestyle",
    "num": "04",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">04</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Frontier Lifestyle</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Daily Life and Challenges on the Texican Frontier</h2><ul><li>Settlers faced threats from Native American raids and harsh environment</li><li>Communities relied on farming, ranching, and trade for survival</li><li>Social life blended Mexican customs with Anglo-American traditions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Life on the Texican frontier was difficult and required resilience. Settlers adapted to environmental challenges and cultural blending, creating a unique frontier lifestyle (s8, s9). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican families built fortified homes and community watch systems to protect against raids.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify key survival strategies used by Texicans in frontier conditions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming frontier life was uniformly hostile without social or cultural adaptation.</p></div></div>",
