    "id": "slide17",
    "eyebrow": "Native American Interactions",
    "num": "05",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">05</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Native American Interactions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Relations with Native American Tribes</h2><ul><li>Interactions ranged from trade and alliances to conflict and raids</li><li>Some tribes resisted settlement encroachment fiercely</li><li>Texicans sometimes adopted Native practices for survival</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlers lived alongside diverse Native American tribes, leading to complex relationships that influenced frontier security and culture (s7, s9). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Trade exchanges between Texicans and tribes included horses, food, and weapons.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Texican-Native relations affected settlement stability.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Portraying Native Americans only as hostile without recognizing alliances or cultural exchange.</p></div></div>",
