    "eyebrow": "Cultural Influences",
    "num": "09",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Influences</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Blending Mexican and Anglo-American Traditions</h2><ul><li>Texicans practiced Catholicism alongside Anglo customs</li><li>Language and legal systems reflected Mexican influence</li><li>Social customs and economic activities showed Anglo-American roots</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican culture was a hybrid, combining Mexican legal and religious frameworks with Anglo-American social and economic practices (s7, s8). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican settlers celebrated Mexican religious festivals while using English in daily communication.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify examples of cultural blending in Texican communities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texicans were culturally homogeneous or purely Anglo-American.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide21\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39; during the Mexican Texas period?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A Mexican citizen living in Texas between 1820 and 1836&quot;,&quot;An Anglo-American settler who moved to Texas after 1836&quot;,&quot;A resident of Texas after it became a U.S. state&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe in Texas&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; specifically referred to Mexican citizens residing in Texas during the Mexican provincial period before Texas independence.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain the role of empresarios like Stephen F. Austin in the settlement patterns of Texicans and how this influenced their lifestyle.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should describe empresarios as land agents authorized by the Mexican government to bring settlers, mention Stephen F. Austin&#39;s key role, and explain how this led to Anglo-Mexican cultural blending and frontier challenges.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Empresarios such as Stephen F. Austin were granted land by the Mexican government to recruit settlers, mainly Anglo-Americans, to colonize Texas. This system shaped Texican settlement patterns by creating communities that blended Mexican and Anglo cultures and faced frontier hardships like conflicts with Native Americans and isolation.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Empresarios brought settlers to Texas under Mexican land grants, influencing Texican settlement and culture.&quot;,&quot;Stephen F. Austin was a key empresario who helped establish Texican communities with mixed cultural backgrounds.&quot;,&quot;The empresario system led to frontier lifestyles with challenges such as Native American conflicts and cultural blending.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
