    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Identity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Group Discussion Activity: Exploring Texican Identity Complexities</h2><ul><li>Analyze primary source letters and secondary narratives in small groups</li><li>Discuss how cultural blending and internal divisions shaped Texican identity</li><li>Share insights on the challenges of defining a hybrid cultural identity</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Collaborative discussion deepens understanding by allowing learners to explore multiple perspectives and articulate their interpretations of Texican identity complexities. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Groups identify examples of cultural blending and political tension in provided texts and discuss their implications.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> In your group, debate whether Texican identity was more unified or divided and why.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Dominating discussion with one viewpoint without considering others.</p></div></div>",
