    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">23</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Identity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Practice Exercise: Identifying Texican Cultural Traits</h2><ul><li>Review descriptions of cultural practices and political views</li><li>Classify each as Anglo, Mexican, or Texican influenced</li><li>Discuss how these traits illustrate blended identity</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This exercise reinforces recognition of Texican cultural hybridity by analyzing specific traits and their origins. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A practice item: Celebrating both Mexican Independence Day and American Thanksgiving reflects Texican cultural blending.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Complete the classification and justify your choices with evidence.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Misclassifying traits by ignoring the hybrid nature of Texican culture.</p></div></div>",
