    "num": "28",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Role in Texas Revolution</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans’ Contributions to the Texas Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texicans played key roles in organizing militias and political conventions</li><li>They negotiated alliances with Anglo settlers and Native groups</li><li>Texican leaders were instrumental in declaring Texas independence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans were central actors in the Texas Revolution, leveraging their political experience and local knowledge. They helped organize resistance, build coalitions, and articulate the case for independence (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican delegates participated in the Convention of 1836, which declared Texas independence from Mexico.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify specific Texican actions that advanced the independence movement and explain their significance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring Texican leadership roles underestimates their influence in the revolution.</p></div></div>",
