    "eyebrow": "Political Timeline",
    "num": "29",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">29</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Timeline</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Key Political Events Involving Texicans (1820–1836)</h2><ul><li>1821: Mexican independence creates new governance context for Texas</li><li>1824: Mexican Constitution establishes Coahuila y Texas province</li><li>1830: Law of April 6 restricts immigration, heightening tensions</li><li>1835–1836: Texas Revolution culminates in independence declaration</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This timeline highlights major political milestones affecting Texicans, illustrating the evolving relationship with Mexican authorities and the path to independence (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The 1830 immigration law directly challenged Texican settlement growth, fueling political unrest.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Construct a timeline of Texican political developments and explain how each event influenced their political stance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Failing to connect political events to Texican responses can obscure cause-effect relationships.</p></div></div>",
