    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">32</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Challenges</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Obstacles Faced by Texicans in Political Sphere</h2><ul><li>Mexican centralization efforts limited Texican political autonomy</li><li>Conflicting loyalties created internal divisions</li><li>External pressures from Anglo settlers and Native tribes complicated politics</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans navigated a challenging political environment marked by Mexican centralization, internal factionalism, and external pressures, which complicated their pursuit of political goals (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Centralist Mexican policies reduced provincial powers, frustrating Texican leaders seeking local control.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify and analyze the main political obstacles Texicans encountered and their responses.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Underestimating the complexity of Texican political challenges leads to simplistic historical interpretations.</p></div></div>",
