    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">35</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application Exercise</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Constructing a Texican Political Timeline</h2><ul><li>Use provided events to build a timeline of Texican political developments</li><li>Analyze how each event influenced Texican political strategies</li><li>Discuss the progression from alliance to revolution</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This exercise engages learners in synthesizing political events and understanding their impact on Texican history through timeline construction (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Placing the 1830 immigration law before the 1835 Texas Revolution shows cause-effect progression.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Create a timeline with key political events and write brief notes on Texican responses to each.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the sequence of events can obscure understanding of political causality.</p></div></div>",
